**Clinical Reasoning:**
Nomograms like MSKCC and CAPRA go beyond simply predicting biochemical recurrence (BCR); they incorporate clinical variables (e.g., Gleason score, PSA, staging) to forecast more directly impactful outcomes such as progression-free survival, lymph node involvement, and ultimately cancer-specific mortality — which aligns closely with clinically relevant endpoints rather than just detecting BCR. Additionally, tools like Prolaris explicitly quantify the 10-year risk of cancer-specific mortality, making them superior predictors of real-world morbidity and mortality compared to BCR alone.

